I spoke to George Mensah - he seemed reluctant to tell me which CBS they are currently on, but does say that they are looking to replace the CBS system next year so there is no point integrating to it. he would like information and I suggested that we visit them during our trip. He says that some decisions will be group and some will be local, we will be part of the decision locally and can promote our system if he likes it. He wants to be sent information and says we can be included in considerations when they begin the process at the end of this year. 
I did not mention Pierre silavant who knows him and Standbic is a customer. part of Standard bank.

Dear Mr Mensah, 

Thank you for your time on the phone today. As discussed, I understand Standbic Bank will undergo a selection process to implement a new core banking system, to include a front office dealing system and this implementation is planned for 2013. Would you mind telling me when you will begin a formal process to choose a system so that I can contact you at this time and I hope we can be included in your considerations? 
As discussed I am speaking with various banks in Accra regarding our Siena Front Office solution, there is a high level of interest and we will be visiting the area in the next 6 weeks in order to have further presentations and begin implementation talks with these banks. 
As a typical example we have implemented the Siena Front Office with Zenith Bank London last year who use the T24 core banking system to automate all dealer activities. We also implemented the Reuters RTNS and TOF capabilities for their Reuters dealing functions to communicate directly with the back office. Our solution is low cost and can be deployed swiftly and we have proven integration capabilities with T24, Flexcube and Midas systems. 
I have attached two documents for you to read which I think will give you a better summary of our Siena Front Office. I would also like to suggest that we meet with you during out visit to Accra. I understand you are not looking to deliver a new solution until 2013 however it would be ideal for us to be introduced and I hope in your best interests to have a greater understanding of which proven soIutions are available to you. I  think it is important that we show you the strength of our solution, both functionally, and in terms of usability and also our ability to successfully take an organisation from a manual style of trading operation, into an automated front office operation.
I have included an information sheet about the Siena Front Office and a recent case study describing the Zenith Bank implementation. I hope to hear

He said they have just rebuilt T24 but there was not much to offer in terms of front office, they have 20 users in the Treasury team this includes dealers and middle office. The cover all FX, MM on individual desks and he specifically said can books be segregated for teams - yes we can. He said the biggest issue for him was to cover commercial and customer needs and they have a new environment with T24 - Temenos are offering a front office system but he does not like having one provider run all of the work flow, he would like to look at other vendors now, his IT manager aggrees. His IT manager is CIO Mr Korodimos who he spoke to this morning about our email and I saw that he downloaded the SFO data sheet too this morning. Mr Athanassios says they are both keen to develop discussions with us and are in a good place to buy, he says they have been struggling in Greece with low productivity in the treasury but things are getting better. 
They have multiple price engines and venues they trade with, reuters, bloomberg and other banks ECNs. 
We have discussed the cost proposal I will send, he has told me to call the CIO in the morning as well to make sure I involve him and have all the info. Then send proposal, he is interested in a presentation but not ready to book this as he would like to arrange it with all in the treasury, IT and Back office. Will call CIO in the morning get further info and deliver the propsal next week.
